  "text": "Animal studies indicate the possibility of multigenerational inheritance related to nutrition and metabolism. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Very few human studies have examined multigenerational effects. In 1 study, generation 1 body mass index (BMI) was directly linked to generation 2 birthweight and BMI, but not third generation BMI, nor did metabolic syndrome in the first generation produce any changes in the birthweight of generations 2 or 3.",
